content: Need a save feature so progress doesn't get lost if your phone rings or something, otherwise fantastic app
Thanks for making this. After buying the physical ga!e, I was sad to see that the physical solo option was out of print. So glad this was made.

It looks nice, but there are a couple of issues: 1. I can't save, so when I have a break in my game and continue later, I have to start a new solo deck - hence my 3 star rating (as is, this is not a good substitute for the physical solo deck). Hopefully a save feature will be added soon. 2. There's 21 cards, not 23. I'm assuming the missing two cards are used for the expansion locations (?). If so, there's no option for including or excluding them.
Is it just me or there are only 21 different cards rather that 23? Despite this I loved it.
A simple but very functional app. My only gripe, it does include rules for the expansions but not cards so the AI will not raid or block new locations.
Great app that looks great, runs well, and enables you to play the tabletop version of Raiders of the North Sea solo with an AI player. App interface really fits the feel of the game.
So excited this was made available. Adds to an already fantastic board game!!
